main event: An unidentified flying object was spotted over Waikiki Beach, Hawaii on January 16, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as looking like a child's balloon, pearl white in color., The object was traveling at an estimated high speed of 3,000 m.p.h., There was no visible trail or exhaust., The sighting lasted for approximately 5 seconds., The conclusion drawn was that it was a daylight meteor.
sighted object: one pearl white object resembling a child's balloon
witness description: The observer is a civilian who provided an account of the sighting.
